100 grams Greek Style Cheese
2 sachet(s) Olives
2 unit(s) Tomato
1 unit(s) Cucumber
4 unit(s) Bamboo Skewers
30 grams Green Pesto
1 sachet(s) Balsamic Glaze
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Oil

Trim the cucumber and chop into thirds.
Chop the tomatoes into 2cm chunks.
Pop the cucumber and tomato into a bowl and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cut the Greek style cheese into 2cm cubes.
Take half the skewers and halve widthways with the help of a scissors.

Thread olives, tomatoes, Greek style cheese and cucumber pieces onto each skewer.
Repeat until you've used all your skewers and all your veg.

Serve the skewers on platters.
Finish with a drizzle of pesto and balsamic glaze.